<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1505,1638]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
Including new species described herein, the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[728,872,1505,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Proctophyllodidae" genus="Amerodectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,872,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Amerodectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presently includes 36 species (Table 1). A key to almost all previously known species, except those described in the past five years, was provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mironov" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" refString="Mironov, S. V. &amp; Gonzalez-Acuna, D. A. (2011) New feather mites of the subfamily Pterodectinae (Astigmata: Proctophyllodidae) from passerines (Aves: Passeriformes) from Chile and Cuba. Zootaxa, 3057, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="2011">Mironov &amp; González-Acuña (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. In the present work, we provide a key to species recorded in the USA and Canada and potentially expected species, based on the presence of corresponding bird hosts in these countries.
</paragraph>
